 Drake 和 J. Cole 的《第一人称射击游戏》首次登上公告牌百强单曲榜榜首，并与 Drake 和 Michael Jackson 并列新纪录https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/drake-j-cole-first-person-shooter-number-one-debut-hot-100-1235443511/  Mon, 16 Oct 2023 17:18:06 +0000 Chart BeatMusic https://www.billboard.com/?p=1235443511 Drake ties Jackson with 13 Hot 100 leaders, the most among solo males, while J. Cole earns his first.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/drake/"  >Drake</a>与<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/j-cole/"  >J. Cole</a>合作的《第一人称射击游戏》在<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100"  >公告牌热门 100</a>歌曲排行榜上名列第一。此次与 Drake 的 LP <em>For All the Dogs</em>的合作——这张专辑首次亮相就在<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/"  >Billboard 200</a>专辑排行榜上<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/drake-for-all-the-dogs-album-number-one-billboard-200-chart-1235442875/"  >排名第一</a>——是他第 13 个登上 Hot 100 排行榜冠军的专辑，与迈克尔·杰克逊 (Michael Jackson) 并列成为该榜单历史上单人男歌手的榜首。在所有行为中排名第四。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> J. Cole 首次登上 Hot 100 排行榜第一名。 </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/drake-pr-02-2023-billboard-1548.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="德雷克" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Drake 凭借《For All the Dogs》第 13 次荣登 Billboard 200 专辑榜第一名</h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 2023年10月16日</time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>与此同时，Drake 的 7 首歌曲跻身 Hot 100 前 10 名，其中包括 6 首首秀歌曲，将他的职业生涯前 10 首单曲总数提高到 76 首。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Hot 100 融合了美国所有类型的流媒体（官方音频和官方视频）、广播电台播放和销售数据，后者反映了从全方位服务数字音乐零售商处购买实体单曲和数字曲目的情况；来自直接面向消费者 (D2C) 网站的数字单曲销量不包含在图表计算中。所有排行榜（日期为 2023 年 10 月 21 日）将于明天（10 月 17 日）在 Billboard.com 上更新。对于所有排行榜新闻，您可以在 X（以前称为 Twitter）和 Instagram 上关注 @billboard 和 @billboardcharts。 </p><figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy" class="youtube-player" width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sRs2o36a1Us?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation"></iframe></div></figure><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>下面让我们来回顾一下《第一人称射击》的加冕，这是该排行榜<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/pro/hot-100-co-creator-seymour-stein-interview/"  >65 年历史</a>上第 1,157 首登上热门 100 强的单曲，也是<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/photos/billboard-hot-100-number-1-song-debuts-426225/68-jung-kook-of-bts-seven-press-credit-bighit-music-2023-billboard-1-1548/"  >第 72 首首次登顶第一名的</a>单曲。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>流媒体、播放和销售：</strong>美国东部时间 10 月 6 日上午 6 点在 OVO Sound/Republic Records 的<em>For All the Dogs</em>上<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/drake-for-all-the-dogs-album-stream-it-now-1235434666/"  >发布</a>，《第一人称射击游戏》吸引了 4,220 万次流媒体播放和 430 万次广播播放观众印象，并在跟踪中售出 4,000 次下载根据 Luminate 的数据，截至 10 月 12 日的一周。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>该单曲首次亮相就在<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/streaming-songs"  >流媒体歌曲</a>排行榜上排名第一，在<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/digital-song-sales/"  >数字歌曲销量</a>上排名第七。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>德雷克 (Drake) 将 MJ 与第 13 届热门 100 排行榜第一名并列：</strong>排行榜观察者德雷克 (Drake) 在“第一人称射击游戏”中指出，“我距离迈克尔只有一步之遥”，同时还大喊杰克逊 1983 年热门 100 排行榜第一名的经典歌曲“Beat It”。在前一首歌曲首次亮相时，歌词已经过时了，因为德雷克现在与杰克逊并列成为独唱男性中最多的领先者：各 13 名。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>自 1958 年 8 月 4 日上榜以来，Drake 和 Jackson 在所有艺人中并列 Hot 100 排行榜第四位。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>大多数公告牌热门 100 位第一名：</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> 20、披头士乐队</li><li>19、玛丽亚·凯莉</li><li>14、蕾哈娜</li><li>13、德雷克</li><li>13、迈克尔·杰克逊</li><li>12、麦当娜</li><li>12、至高无上</li><li>11、惠特尼·休斯顿</li><li>10、珍妮·杰克逊</li><li>10、史蒂夫·旺德</li></ul></div><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/drake-pr-2023-billboard-1548.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="德雷克" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max">德雷克说他“可能不会做一点音乐”来专注于...... </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 2023年10月16日</time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>以下是 Drake 13 场热门 100 名第一的回顾：</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> “第一人称射击游戏”，德雷克壮举。 J. Cole（至今一周，2023 年 10 月 21 日）</li><li> “把你粘出来”，德雷克的壮举。 SZA（一周，2023年9月30日）</li><li> “吉米·库克”，德雷克的壮举。 21 Savage（一周，2022年7月2日）</li><li> “等待你”，未来的壮举。 Drake 和 Tems（一周，2022 年 5 月 14 日）</li><li> “Way 2 sexy”，德雷克壮举。未来与年轻暴徒（一周，2021年9月18日）</li><li> “下一步是什么”，Drake（一周，2021 年 3 月 20 日）</li><li> “Toosie Slide”，德雷克（一周，2020 年 4 月 18 日）</li><li> “In My Feelings”，Drake（10 周，从 2018 年 7 月 21 日开始）</li><li> “Nice for What”，Drake（八周，从 2018 年 4 月 21 日开始）</li><li> “God&#39;s Plan,” Drake (11 weeks, beginning Feb. 3, 2018)</li><li> “One Dance,” Drake feat. WizKid &amp; Kyla (10 weeks, beginning May 21, 2016)</li><li> “Work,” Rihanna feat. Drake (nine weeks, beginning March 5, 2016)</li><li> “What&#39;s My Name?,” Rihanna feat. Drake (one week at No. 1, beginning Nov. 20, 2010)</li></ul></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>J. Cole&#39;s first No. 1:</strong> J. Cole earns his first Hot 100 No. 1, with his 72nd entry on the chart. He previously reached No. 2 twice, as featured on Lil Durk&#39;s “All My Life” (this May) and with “my.life,” with 21 Savage and Morray (May 2021). As “First Person Shooter” debuts, he now totals 12 career top 10s.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Drake&#39;s record ninth No. 1 debut:</strong> “First Person Shooter” is Drake&#39;s record-extending ninth song to debut at No. 1 on the Hot 100. He previously started at the top with “Slime You Out,” “Jimmy Cooks,” “Wait for U,” “Way 2 Sexy,” “What&#39;s Next,” “Toosie Slide,” “Nice for What” and “God&#39;s Plan.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Drake passes BTS for most No. 1s in the &#39;20s:</strong> Drake ups his haul to seven Hot 100 No. 1s in the 2020s – pushing him past BTS for the most so far this decade. Ariana Grande and Taylor Swift follow with four each in that span.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Drake earned six Hot 100 No. 1s in the &#39;10s, the fourth-best sum, after Rihanna (nine), Katy Perry (eight) and Bruno Mars (seven).</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Here&#39;s a recap of the artists with the most Hot 100 leaders in each decade:</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> &#39;20s, to date: Drake, seven</li><li> &#39;10s: Rihanna, nine</li><li> &#39;00s: Usher, seven</li><li> &#39;90s: Mariah Carey, 14</li><li> &#39;80s: Michael Jackson, nine</li><li> &#39;70s: Bee Gees, nine</li><li> &#39;60s: The Beatles, 18</li></ul></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> (Frankie Avalon and The Fleetwoods tied for the most Hot 100 No. 1s, two each, over 1958-59.)</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Drake claims 7 of top 10:</strong> Drake tallies seven songs overall in the latest Hot 100&#39;s top 10. He infuses the entire top three for a third time (after he tripled up on the Sept. 18, 2021, and March 20, 2021, charts). He and The Beatles (five weeks, 1964) are the only acts with multiple such weeks, while Grande and Swift have monopolized the top three once each.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Here&#39;s a rundown of Drake&#39;s tracks in the latest Hot 100&#39;s top 10 (all of which are debuts except for No. 6):</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> No. 1, “First Person Shooter,” feat. J. Cole</li><li> No. 2, “IDGAF,” feat. Yeat</li><li> No. 3, “Virginia Beach”</li><li> No. 5, “Calling for You,” feat. 21 Savage</li><li> No. 6, “Slime You Out,” feat. SZA (up from No. 18; <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/drake-sza-slime-you-out-hot-100-number-one-debut-1235420205/"  >debuted at No. 1</a> on the Sept. 30 chart)</li><li> No. 8, “Daylight”</li><li> No. 10, “Fear of Heights”</li></ul></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> As J. Cole lands his first Hot 100 No. 1, and 12th top 10, Yeat earns his first top 10 and 21 Savage, his 15th (and 10th in collaboration with Drake). </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/drake-sxa-a-billboard-1548.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="Sza and Drake" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Ask Billboard: As Drake &amp; SZA Debut, Which Hot 100 No. 1s Have Had the Most Star Power? </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 10/16/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Drake&#39;s records in top 2, 5 &amp; 10:</strong> “First Person Shooter” also contributes to Drake&#39;s marks for the most top two, top five and top 10 Hot 100 hits.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Here&#39;s an updated look at Drake&#39;s leading ranks among acts with the most hits in those tiers:</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> <em>Top 2:</em> Now with 23 top two Hot 100 hits, Drake ties The Beatles and Mariah Carey for the most. (The Beatles boast 20 No. 1s, the most among all acts, and three top two hits; Carey has 19 and four, respectively; and Drake now has 13 and a record 10, respectively.)</li><li> <em>Top 5</em> : Now with 41 top five Hot 100 hits, Drake moves further ahead of runners-up The Beatles (29). Madonna follows with 28.</li><li> <em>Top 10:</em> Now with 76 top 10 Hot 100 hits, Drake surges further past Swift, in second place with 42. Madonna is next with 38.</li></ul></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>No. 1 on Streaming Songs, R&amp;B/hip-hop charts:</strong> As “First Person Shooter” concurrently crowns the Streaming Songs chart, Drake adds his record-extending 19th No. 1. (Justin Bieber and Swift rank next with six each.) J. Cole notches his second No. 1, after “Interlude” led for a week in May 2021.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “First Person Shooter” likewise premieres atop the <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/r-b-hip-hop-songs/"  >Hot R&amp;B/Hip-Hop Songs</a> and <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/rap-song/"  >Hot Rap Songs</a> charts, which use the same multi-metric methodology as the Hot 100. Drake claims his record-padding 30th Hot R&amp;B/Hip-Hop Songs No. 1, further distancing himself from legends Aretha Franklin and Stevie Wonder, each with 20. J. Cole collects his third Hot R&amp;B/Hip-Hop Songs No. 1, after “All My Life” ruled for seven weeks and “my.life,” for one frame. On Hot Rap Songs, Drake and J. Cole also swell their No. 1 totals to a record-extending 30 and three, respectively.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Plus, on the multi-metric <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/r-and-b-songs/"  >Hot R&amp;B Songs</a> chart, “Slime You Out” rebounds for a second week at No. 1.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>&#39;First&#39; things first:</strong> Last but not least, “First Person Shooter” is the fifth Hot 100 No. 1 with the word “first” in its title. Here&#39;s an updated firsthand look:</p><div class="container // lrv-a-font-body-m lrv-u-margin-lr-auto   "><ul><li> “First Person Shooter,” Drake feat. J. Cole, one week at No. 1, beginning Oct. 21, 2023</li><li> “First Class,” Jack Harlow, three weeks, beginning April 23, 2022</li><li> “The First Night,” Monica, five weeks, beginning Oct. 3, 1998</li><li> “The First Time,” Surface, two weeks, beginning Jan. 26, 1991</li><li> “The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face,” Roberta Flack, six weeks, beginning April 15, 1972</li></ul></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Elsewhere, three songs not by Drake make the latest Hot 100&#39;s top 10, led by Doja Cat&#39;s “Paint the Town Red,” which falls to No. 4 following three nonconsecutive weeks at No. 1.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> SZA&#39;s “Snooze” retreats to No. 7 on the Hot 100 from its No. 2 high. It rules the <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/radio-songs/"  >Radio Songs</a> chart for a second week (77.9 million in audience, up 3%).</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Plus, Swift&#39;s “Cruel Summer” slips to No. 9 on the Hot 100 from its No. 3 peak.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Again, for all chart news, you can follow @billboard and @billboardcharts on both Twitter and Instagram and all charts (dated Oct. 21), including the Hot 100 in its entirety, will refresh on Billboard.com tomorrow (Oct. 17).</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
